      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/en/tutorial-create-repo/intro.d4921d84.mp3",
      "narrationText": "Let's create your first repository! It's an encrypted file at rest that turns into a fully isolated environment the moment you create it.",
      "audioDurationSec": 8.907755
    },
    {
      "id": "file-on-disk",
      "textHash": "5083fa2473639e24068e94fe8890f45aafd8cde7de1b11ded47ff40b012a8c43",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/en/tutorial-create-repo/file-on-disk.5083fa24.mp3",
      "narrationText": "On disk it's a single encrypted image. Once mounted, you get a dedicated Docker daemon, application data inside the encrypted volume, and loopback IPs that won't collide with anything else on the server.",
      "audioDurationSec": 13.714286
    },
    {
